
Labeling Form Helper
====================
Contributors:
- Seth Thomas Rasmussen : http://sethrasmussen.com : sethrasmussen@gmail.com
- Jeremy Kemper
====================

Adds auto-labeling with some custom options to Rails' form helpers by extending ActionView::Helpers::FormBuilder and ActionView::Helpers::FormTagHelper.

  builder.text_field :foo, :label => 'yeah, foo'
  # <label for="foo">yeah, foo</label><input ... />

All of the original helper options are available, with some additional ones for customizing the output of the label and the tag.

    :label       => text between label tags. pass +false+ to disable label generation - default: attribute_name.humanize
    :label_wrap  => whether or not the label closes before or after the input - default: false
    :label_after => whether or not the the label text appears before or after the input. :label_wrap must be true for this option to apply - default: false
    
To enable the LabelingFormBuilder:

    ActionView::Base.default_form_builder = LabelingFormBuilder # from just about anywhere, probably environment.rb or an initializer
    
To enable the LabelingFormTagHelper:

    include LabelingFormTagHelper # from another helper, e.g. ApplicationHelper
    helper :labeling_form_tag     # from a controller, e.g. ApplicationController

Yay! Making forms sucks even less now!
